What will be the output of the following JavaScript code?

<p id="demo"></p>
<script>
var txt1 = "good";
var txt2 = "day";
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = txt1 + txt2;
</script>

What will be the output of the following JavaScript code?

<p id="demo"></p>
<script>
var x = 5;
var y = 2;
var z = x % y;
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = z;
</script>

